The paper deals with image recognition tasks using convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision and machine learning. The focus of the paper is on semantic segmentation, which is a subfield of computer vision that involves identifying and labeling different parts of an image. The paper also discusses the use of modular neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Other likely sub-categories include cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.MM (Multimedia).
